We are excited to announce that the long-awaited @adamjones_tv and @epiphone partnership has arrived with the Epiphone Adam Jones Art Collection. This new limited-edition collection blends Adam’s love of fine art and music, resulting in seven Silverburst Les Paul Custom masterpieces. Adam curated the five distinguished artists featured in the collection, and each guitar features artwork designed by artist Korin Faught on the back of the headstock. Only 800 guitars of each model will be produced. 
 
The first model available in this exciting series is the Adam Jones Les Paul Custom Art Collection: Mark Ryden’s “The Veil of Bees.” This model features Mark Ryden’s “The Veil of Bees” on the back. Blending themes of pop culture with techniques of the old masters, @markryden blurs the traditional boundaries between high and low art in a new genre of “Pop Surrealism.” 
 
This guitar isn’t just an art piece to hang on your wall; it’s also an exceptional instrument for your next musical masterpiece. Stop by the Gibson Garage to get yours now! 
 
#epiphone #foreverystage #silverburst #lespaul #adamjones #tool #toolmusic #markryden #veilofbees #gibsongarage

Yesterday, January 2, 2023 was an important milestone as I turned 46, the age my father was when he passed away 26 years ago. My birthday is a celebration of my mother Graciela and my father Jorge rather than of me personally. I don’t think I did anything to deserve to be celebrated on January 2, but my Mom and Dad did. So happy “Birth” day to my mother Graciela and thank you to my Dad for the 20 years of EPIC SHIT while I had you #thankyou for exposing me to music, business, sports and family values from an early age! #DES #doepicshit #46 #january and thank you to @amandalchurch #luciano #christian #marcela and all my friends I call #brothers and #sisters

Gibson TV’s award-winning docuseries, “The Process,” is returning for a second season! This time we’re taking you behind the scenes for an in-depth look at the physical process of making our acoustic guitars. “The Process” is an exploration into our newly expanded acoustic factory in Bozeman, MT, featuring interviews with the talented craftspeople that hand-make these beloved guitars and deep dives into the art of guitar making. 
 
In the first episode, “The Process: How Tops, Backs, and Sides Are Created,” Robi Johns, Senior Product Development Manager, and Don Ruffatto, Product Development Manager, walk through the beginning steps of crafting acoustic guitars in a factory that does more handwork than any other major manufacturer. 
 
Click the link in bio or head to Gibson TV on YouTube and watch the full episode to hear the history of the factory and see the passion that goes into each and every guitar. 
 
#gibson #gibsontv #theprocess

When it comes to acoustic guitars, the topic of bracing can be divisive. While some argue that it has no impact on the sound, at Gibson, we believe that the bracing pattern plays a crucial role in shaping the dynamic range and tone of the instrument. Building on the traditions of Orville Gibson, the evolution of Gibson’s bracing and body construction has always been in service to sound. In Season 2, Episode 2 of “The Process,” delve deeper into our approach to bracing and body construction and see for yourself how Gibson’s commitment to sound is woven into every aspect of our guitar-making process. 
 
Click the #linkinbio or head to Gibson TV on YouTube to watch the full episode to hear the factory’s history and see the passion that goes into each and every guitar.

We are excited to announce the next Gibson Certified Vintage guitar available is an original 1960 Les Paul Standard, serial #0 1490. Certified by Gibson as an authentic vintage electric guitar manufactured and shipped in 1960. 

Known as “Sunny,” this sunburst 1960 Les Paul Standard was first sold by its original owner’s widow to a prominent collector in the 1980s, eventually ending up in the possession of Metallica guitarist @KirkHammett, who used it extensively until 2022. 

“Sunny is special because not only is she in immaculate condition, but her tone is so present and bright, it’s like the sun cutting through clouds on an overcast day,” says Kirk. “Hence the name ‘Sunny.’ That’s the truth. The name came because she was so full and bright sounding. 

“The reason I chose Gibson Certified Vintage for the worldwide offering is because having a mint vintage Gibson guitar can sometimes feel like having a brand-new Gibson guitar. They’re made that well. And this is what’s really special; the fact Gibson recognizes this and is willing and ready to re-warranty these beautiful instruments. I think this is just a great reflection of Gibson’s integrity towards the past, present, and future.” 

#gibson #gibsoncertifiedvintage #theoriginal #DES #kirkhammett

I'm currently at our Gibson Acoustic Craftory here in Bozeman, MT visiting with our wonderful craftspeople and would like to take a moment to introduce you all to Kristy Shumaker.
 
Kristy makes our Gibson Acoustic guitar bridges and has quickly become a vital part of our Gibson Family here in Bozeman.  Sadly, Kristy recently lost her 23 year-old son, Noah, but continues to show up and pour her heart and soul into each and every acoustic she touches. I am grateful that Kristy shared her story with me and that she can find some comfort in her and Noah's shared love of music.
 
Please keep Kristy in your thoughts and if you have the time, play a few notes for Noah today.
 
#mentalhealthawareness

I’m humbled and honored to have been confirmed as Gibson President & CEO. I’m grateful for our board, team, fans, family and artists, who have supported me to merge my biggest passion with my business background. 

My responsibility is not only as leader of our Gibson global team, but also as an ambassador for all the passionate people, fans, and artists, around the world, who love music and the guitar as much as I and all of us at Gibson do. 

I look forward to the next Gibson “era”, where I am responsible for leading our team on a path of self-discovery, listening, inspiring, and empowering our talented team to lead us into the future. To leverage our iconic past and lean into the future with passion. To create the conditions for all of us to be more creative the older we become as individuals and as a company.

As you know that I love teaching guitar very much! I enjoy making people smile.
This one is very special! My former student @bengoldsmithmusic he was only 12 when his parents contacted me. I almost said “no” because I generally want to wait till their age around 13-14… but his parents really told me how much Ben loves playing guitar and he loves my YouTube videos. Then they are willing to come here every week! From New York to Boston! Amazing family! I thought it’s crazy! A lot of work for one hour lesson! 

So I accepted it. I taught him all boring foundation stuff at his age 12! No jam! Then Blues, funk, jazz.. good languages of music that I know. I just don’t want to hurry at all. Very slow pace so a lot of patiences on each sides. We did it! Worked very hard together… he kept coming back! We did same thing over and over until I like it. 

Now, is he ready? I think so! He graduated from his high school in this year. And he got signed with Sony music!! Wow!! I am proud of Ben so much! Thanks for your patience on these years. I pushed a lot of things to you. Congratulations on your new journey! Now you can fly yourself! We’re friends forever🙏❤️🙏

PS, Very kind heart @gueikian shared this post on his Instagram account. I am so grateful and thankful today❤️🙏❤️
